                  <additions>
                     <list>
                        <item xml:id="a1">
                           <locus target="#229rc"/>
                           <q xml:lang="gez"/>
                           <t:desc xmlns:t="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" type="DonationNote">Donation note, mentioning the name of the donor, <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS14882Elleni">ʾƎlleni</persName> ʻalso called Walatta Qālʼ (probably her baptismal name) 
                              who was the mother of <t:roleName type="title">ʾAbeto</t:roleName> <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS14883Abeselom">ʾAbeselom</persName> and the wife of <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS14884NewayaMary">Nǝwāya Māryām</persName>. 
                              The note tells that the donation was made upon the advice of ʾAbuna <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS14885WalAbiEgz">Walda ʾAbiya ʾƎgziʾ</persName>, probably a monk from the monastery. 
                              It mentions also that the donation was permitted by a certain <t:roleName type="rank">Daǧǧāzmāč</t:roleName> <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS14886Berru">Bǝrru</persName>. </t:desc>
                           <t:quote xmlns:t="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xml:lang="gez"> ዘሠረቆ፡ ወዘረሐቆ፡ ውጉዘ፡ ለይኩን። ዝመጽሐፍ፡
                              ዘአቤቶ፡ አቤሴሎም፡ ስመ፡ አቡሁ፡ ንዋየ፡ ማርያም፡ ወሰመ፡ እሙ፡ እሌኒ፡ ወዓዲ፡ ትትበሐል፡ ወለተ፡ ቃል፡
                              ወይእቲ፡ ወሀበቶ፡ ለመካነ፡ አረጋዊ፡ በምክረ፡ አቡነ፡ ወልደ፡ አቢየ፡ እግዚእ፡ ወበፈቃደ፡ ደጃዝማች፡ ብሩ፡
                              ዘውእቱ፡ ወልደ፡ አቢየ፡ እግዚእ፡ ከመ፡ ይኵና፡ መርሐ፡ በመንግሥተ፡ ሰማያት፡ ላቲ፡ ወለደቂቃ።</t:quote>
                           <note> </note>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="a2">
                           <locus target="#230v"/>
                           <q xml:lang="am"/>
                           <t:desc xmlns:t="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" type="RecordReconciliation">Record concerning reconciliation between Christians and Muslims. The note was written in a secondary hand during the time
                              of King <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS7006Menilek">Mǝnilǝk</persName> (r. <date>1889‒1913</date>) and the tenure of <t:roleName type="title">ʾAbbot</t:roleName> <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS14887KidMary">Kidāna Māryām</persName>.</t:desc>
                         
                           
                        </item>
